===Idiom===

'''[[run]] [[something]] [[into]] the [[ground]]'''

# To [[mismanage]] something to the point of ruin. 
#: ''Although he has an MBA from Harvard, he still '''ran the company into the ground'''.''
# To use something until it is no longer functions properly. 
#: ''I figure this car has has a few more years left in it and I intend to '''run it into the ground''' before purchasing another.''
# To discuss something [[ad nauseum]].
#: ''You've '''run the upcoming election into the ground''' and I simply won't listen to another word about it.''

